This article is about an executive order signed by President Barack Obama to strengthen the Senior Executive Service (SES) of the Federal Government. The order aims to improve the recruitment, hiring, and development of senior executives, increase diversity and inclusion in the workforce, and enhance executive accountability. It establishes a Subcommittee to advise on senior executive matters and monitor the execution of executive reforms. The order also outlines specific requirements for agencies to limit spending on performance awards, implement policies for pay setting and adjustments, streamline application requirements for SES positions, and develop talent management and succession planning processes. It further calls for the establishment of an Executive Onboarding Program and regular reporting on the status of implementation.